WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.985 --> 00:00:02.996
<i>Previously on</i> Vikings...

2
00:00:03.020 --> 00:00:04.236
Uncle!

3
00:00:04.305 --> 00:00:06.972
The bear will be
crowned by a princess.

4
00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:10.342
which does not bode
well for you. King Ragnar.

5
00:00:10.411 --> 00:00:14.462
When everyone wanted
you dead. I kept you alive!

6
00:00:14.531 --> 00:00:17.299
And this is how
you repay my love?

7
00:00:17.384 --> 00:00:18.794
Erlendur has
told me to kill you.

8
00:00:18.818 --> 00:00:19.938
What are you waiting for?

9
00:00:22.540 --> 00:00:23.867
I want to sleep
with your sister.

10
00:00:23.891 --> 00:00:25.290
Of course. Your Highness.

11
00:00:25.358 --> 00:00:26.975
There is something else.

12
00:00:27.044 --> 00:00:29.127
I understand that your
brother betrayed you.

13
00:00:29.196 --> 00:00:31.946
<i>That he stands
between us and Paris.</i>

14
00:00:32.033 --> 00:00:35.600
To the first child of our
Frankish-Viking alliance.

15
00:00:35.669 --> 00:00:37.553
Paris cannot be
taken without you.

16
00:00:37.621 --> 00:00:39.621
I don't care about Paris.

17
00:00:39.690 --> 00:00:41.072
I came for Rollo.

18
00:00:44.778 --> 00:00:46.145
I will kill you.

19
00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:54.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

20
00:01:46.056 --> 00:01:47.189
Pull!

21
00:01:48.976 --> 00:01:49.992
Pull!

22
00:01:54.381 --> 00:01:55.981
Pull right!

23
00:02:01.455 --> 00:02:03.755
This is of your doing. Rollo.

24
00:02:18.672 --> 00:02:20.038
Look. upriver!

25
00:02:42.045 --> 00:02:43.278
I can see.

26
00:02:45.966 --> 00:02:47.833
Raise the standards.

27
00:02:47.902 --> 00:02:49.785
FRANKISH CAPTAIN
1: Raise your standards!

28
00:02:49.853 --> 00:02:51.954
FRANKISH CAPTAIN
2: Raise your standards!

29
00:02:57.577 --> 00:02:59.378
Sound the horns!

30
00:03:04.301 --> 00:03:07.669
Prepare to move
alongside and board!

31
00:03:19.315 --> 00:03:20.766
Front line!

32
00:03:21.368 --> 00:03:22.801
Advance!

33
00:03:37.935 --> 00:03:39.835
May God be with us.

34
00:03:48.895 --> 00:03:53.114
From the fury of the
Northmen. O Lord. deliver us.

35
00:03:54.384 --> 00:03:58.020
We commit ourselves
into the hands of our Lord.

36
00:03:58.088 --> 00:04:00.856
We know that the
Lord. our God. will smite

37
00:04:00.941 --> 00:04:03.008
and deliver us from our enemies.

38
00:04:03.077 --> 00:04:04.626
Glory be to God.

39
00:04:04.694 --> 00:04:07.846
Glory be to God.

40
00:04:07.898 --> 00:04:12.667
Holy Mother. I beg you.
don't forget my husband.

41
00:04:12.736 --> 00:04:17.422
I carry his child.
a Christian child.

42
00:04:17.491 --> 00:04:21.809
Holy Mother. you
can forgive all sins.

43
00:04:21.878 --> 00:04:25.864
And so I ask
you. in all humility.

44
00:04:25.933 --> 00:04:31.202
to forgive and protect
my beloved husband.

45
00:04:31.271 --> 00:04:34.973
who. at this hour. is also trying
to protect this place of worship

46
00:04:35.042 --> 00:04:37.492
and all these Christian people.

47
00:04:57.164 --> 00:04:58.880
Bowmen. to your stations!

48
00:05:12.796 --> 00:05:13.812
Ready!

49
00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:16.898
First rank!

50
00:05:16.967 --> 00:05:18.033
Loose!

51
00:05:25.509 --> 00:05:27.976
Loose arrows!

52
00:05:31.198 --> 00:05:33.681
Second rank! Loose!

53
00:05:37.370 --> 00:05:39.821
Third rank! Loose!

54
00:05:39.906 --> 00:05:40.972
Loose!

55
00:05:42.258 --> 00:05:43.258
Fourth rank!

56
00:05:43.694 --> 00:05:44.759
Ready!

57
00:05:44.828 --> 00:05:45.977
Loose!

58
00:05:47.063 --> 00:05:50.148
Fourth rank! Loose!

59
00:05:54.938 --> 00:05:56.354
Advance!

60
00:06:35.779 --> 00:06:37.111
Charge!

61
00:08:12.976 --> 00:08:14.604
What are your orders?

62
00:08:14.628 --> 00:08:15.709
My orders?

63
00:08:16.646 --> 00:08:18.112
Shall we break off the attack?

64
00:08:18.949 --> 00:08:20.415
Regather our forces?

65
00:08:22.719 --> 00:08:25.153
"Break off the attack"?

66
00:08:25.221 --> 00:08:28.389
We have already sustained
considerable losses.

67
00:08:28.458 --> 00:08:31.659
Perhaps. in the circumstance. it
would be better if we took ourselves...

68
00:08:49.446 --> 00:08:51.313
All of my life.

69
00:08:52.649 --> 00:08:56.584
and all of your lives.
have come to this point.

70
00:08:58.672 --> 00:09:01.789
There is nowhere
else to be but here.

71
00:09:01.858 --> 00:09:04.625
Nowhere else to
live or die. but here.

72
00:09:04.694 --> 00:09:08.296
To be here now is the
only thing that matters.

73
00:09:10.817 --> 00:09:12.483
So gather yourselves.

74
00:09:12.552 --> 00:09:15.637
gather all of your strength

75
00:09:15.705 --> 00:09:19.473
and all of your
sweetness into an iron ball.

76
00:09:19.542 --> 00:09:23.645
For we will attack
again and again.

77
00:09:23.713 --> 00:09:26.347
Until we reach and
overcome their king.

78
00:09:26.415 --> 00:09:27.882
or we die in the attempt!

79
00:09:28.652 --> 00:09:29.767
We attack!

80
00:09:29.836 --> 00:09:30.836
Attack! Attack! Attack!

81
00:09:32.155 --> 00:09:33.621
Blow the horns!

82
00:09:33.690 --> 00:09:36.608
Beat the drums and have courage.

83
00:09:36.677 --> 00:09:38.493
for there will be
no turning back!

84
00:09:38.561 --> 00:09:41.713
Only victory or death!

85
00:09:46.369 --> 00:09:48.186
What is he going to do?

86
00:09:50.857 --> 00:09:53.177
He'll do what he always does...

87
00:10:00.567 --> 00:10:01.833
Attack.

88
00:10:04.938 --> 00:10:06.370
Ragnar!

89
00:10:07.841 --> 00:10:09.974
Rollo. we're coming for you!

90
00:10:10.543 --> 00:10:11.676
Good.

91
00:10:14.697 --> 00:10:16.564
Let them try.

92
00:10:16.633 --> 00:10:18.099
We are ready.

93
00:10:20.887 --> 00:10:23.405
Row! Faster!

94
00:10:24.741 --> 00:10:25.757
Faster!

95
00:10:45.244 --> 00:10:46.544
I'll live.

96
00:10:47.947 --> 00:10:50.247
Rollo!

97
00:10:50.317 --> 00:10:55.219
Betrayer of the gods and all
the sacred things in Midgard!

98
00:10:55.288 --> 00:10:57.188
Come here. you snake!

99
00:10:57.256 --> 00:11:02.727
Come my way. and let my ax
slake its thirst on your blood.

100
00:11:02.796 --> 00:11:04.462
Come to Floki.

101
00:11:04.531 --> 00:11:07.965
Come to Floki. you
bastard. I am waiting.

102
00:11:09.202 --> 00:11:11.419
Ragnar. what else can be done?

103
00:11:12.855 --> 00:11:15.756
There is nothing
else to be done.

104
00:11:22.549 --> 00:11:24.282
Do the gods favor us?

105
00:11:26.119 --> 00:11:28.503
Of course they favor us.

106
00:11:28.571 --> 00:11:32.474
How could they favor Rollo
after he renounced them?

107
00:11:32.559 --> 00:11:35.860
I just need to hear it
from your father's mouth.

108
00:11:40.299 --> 00:11:44.669
Row! Row! Row!

109
00:11:44.737 --> 00:11:46.521
Faster.

110
00:11:49.159 --> 00:11:50.274
Faster!

111
00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:25.009
Even as we sit here.
eating and drinking.

112
00:12:25.077 --> 00:12:27.845
Duke Rollo and our forces
are engaged with the enemy.

113
00:12:28.648 --> 00:12:29.930
I know.

114
00:12:29.999 --> 00:12:31.377
And I have made
every effort to make sure

115
00:12:31.401 --> 00:12:32.611
that. if the Duke should fail.

116
00:12:32.635 --> 00:12:35.252
Paris will still be
well-defended.

117
00:12:35.321 --> 00:12:37.249
Your Highness should be
assured that you are not completely

118
00:12:37.273 --> 00:12:39.040
dependent upon a Northman.

119
00:12:39.108 --> 00:12:42.360
I rather like being
dependent on a Northman.

120
00:12:43.830 --> 00:12:45.396
They tend to tell the truth.

121
00:12:47.901 --> 00:12:50.301
Your grandfather
warned against them.

122
00:12:50.370 --> 00:12:52.665
He said they were the greatest
threat against his empire.

123
00:12:52.689 --> 00:12:58.243
My grandfather. wise as
he was. great as he was.

124
00:12:59.579 --> 00:13:01.813
did not understand everything.

125
00:13:03.933 --> 00:13:05.917
Times change.

126
00:13:05.986 --> 00:13:08.085
But the threat of the
Northmen remains!

127
00:13:08.154 --> 00:13:10.274
Of course it
remains. poor Roland.

128
00:13:12.325 --> 00:13:13.625
And yet.

129
00:13:13.693 --> 00:13:15.076
I trust Duke Rollo.

130
00:13:15.912 --> 00:13:17.761
I trust him completely.

131
00:13:18.965 --> 00:13:20.081
I have his heart.

132
00:13:21.017 --> 00:13:22.366
and he has mine.

133
00:13:23.119 --> 00:13:24.279
He has your heart?

134
00:13:24.804 --> 00:13:26.237
Yes.

135
00:13:26.305 --> 00:13:27.538
He has my heart.

136
00:13:27.607 --> 00:13:29.523
Don't be so stupid!

137
00:13:29.592 --> 00:13:31.876
Ah! There is the truth.

138
00:13:31.945 --> 00:13:33.828
I am stupid. after all.

139
00:13:36.015 --> 00:13:38.499
And not. as I
thought. merely weak.

140
00:13:38.568 --> 00:13:40.434
Merely vacillating.

141
00:13:40.503 --> 00:13:41.869
Indecisive.

142
00:13:44.191 --> 00:13:46.925
It has. indeed. taken me
a long time to understand

143
00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:48.492
who my real friends truly are.

144
00:13:52.632 --> 00:13:54.532
Now.

145
00:13:54.601 --> 00:13:56.851
we must have something
to finish our meal.

146
00:13:56.919 --> 00:13:58.435
I'm not hungry.

147
00:13:58.504 --> 00:14:00.544
It doesn't matter. Count Roland.

148
00:14:02.108 --> 00:14:05.509
Where you and your bitch are
going. you can eat angel's wings.

149
00:14:47.420 --> 00:14:51.673
Put your backs
into it! Row! Row!

150
00:15:29.595 --> 00:15:31.562
Prepare to breach!

151
00:15:50.683 --> 00:15:52.400
Onward!

152
00:17:38.058 --> 00:17:40.424
Look at you! You
look like a bitch.

153
00:17:42.178 --> 00:17:46.263
You're not my brother.
You never have been.

154
00:17:48.951 --> 00:17:51.418
One of us will die today.

155
00:17:51.487 --> 00:17:54.655
And it won't be me. brother!

156
00:19:40.479 --> 00:19:41.695
Brother!

157
00:19:49.806 --> 00:19:53.357
Odin! Where are you?

158
00:21:27.135 --> 00:21:30.421
Bjorn. get her on the boat!

159
00:21:47.924 --> 00:21:50.308
Come! Cut the ropes.

160
00:21:54.781 --> 00:21:56.530
Get her out of here!

161
00:22:06.109 --> 00:22:08.575
Leave me! Leave me!

162
00:22:17.619 --> 00:22:19.887
Row! Row!

163
00:22:23.576 --> 00:22:24.576
Enough!

164
00:22:27.062 --> 00:22:28.094
Enough!

165
00:22:28.163 --> 00:22:29.562
Let them go!

166
00:24:00.856 --> 00:24:03.006
Rollo! Rollo!

167
00:24:42.748 --> 00:24:44.447
Father!

168
00:24:44.517 --> 00:24:48.852
I present the savior of Paris!

169
00:24:48.921 --> 00:24:50.921
The hero of Frankia!

170
00:25:01.750 --> 00:25:02.916
Stand.

171
00:25:22.337 --> 00:25:24.054
Hail. Caesar!

172
00:25:24.123 --> 00:25:26.489
Hail. Caesar!

173
00:25:26.558 --> 00:25:29.109
Hail. Caesar!

174
00:27:30.016 --> 00:27:31.164
Bjorn!

175
00:27:32.935 --> 00:27:34.618
You'd better come.

176
00:27:55.657 --> 00:27:57.157
Who's this?

177
00:27:57.225 --> 00:27:58.425
His name is Thorhall.

178
00:27:59.995 --> 00:28:01.478
He has come with a story.

179
00:28:03.716 --> 00:28:05.199
I'm listening.

180
00:28:06.502 --> 00:28:09.002
I went on a raiding
party last year to England.

181
00:28:09.071 --> 00:28:11.138
with Earl Gunnar Asgrimsson.

182
00:28:11.207 --> 00:28:14.975
We fought against the armies of
King Ecbert. and wintered in Wessex.

183
00:28:15.043 --> 00:28:16.763
And made a treaty
with Ecbert's ealdormen.

184
00:28:19.614 --> 00:28:23.717
And they told us that
your father. King Ragnar.

185
00:28:23.786 --> 00:28:26.904
had sired a child there by
Queen Kwenthrith of Mercia.

186
00:28:26.972 --> 00:28:29.223
and that this child still
lives at Ecbert's court.

187
00:28:33.078 --> 00:28:34.477
What's the child's name?

188
00:28:34.547 --> 00:28:36.563
Magnus.

189
00:28:36.632 --> 00:28:39.115
He is a young man
now. 12 years old.

190
00:28:47.727 --> 00:28:51.678
And you are certain that this
Magnus is really my father's child?

191
00:28:52.498 --> 00:28:54.030
How can I be certain?

192
00:28:54.100 --> 00:28:55.615
I was not there
at the conception.

193
00:29:01.156 --> 00:29:02.889
Why would they lie?

194
00:29:13.551 --> 00:29:15.463
There was something
else you learned

195
00:29:15.487 --> 00:29:17.567
from Ecbert's
ealdormen. was there not?

196
00:29:19.741 --> 00:29:20.857
Well?

197
00:29:23.195 --> 00:29:26.229
It was about your father's
farming settlement in Wessex.

198
00:29:26.298 --> 00:29:28.849
We asked if it still
existed and they laughed.

199
00:29:28.917 --> 00:29:31.902
and said it was destroyed almost
as soon as your father sailed away.

200
00:29:33.538 --> 00:29:37.507
But that they allowed some
of the settlers to escape.

201
00:29:37.576 --> 00:29:40.794
so they would take the word
to your father. as a warning.

202
00:29:43.816 --> 00:29:44.914
He never mentioned it.

203
00:29:45.718 --> 00:29:47.150
Ask him now.

204
00:29:49.455 --> 00:29:52.305
We don't know where Ragnar is.

205
00:29:52.374 --> 00:29:55.074
He left soon after
his defeat in Paris.

206
00:29:56.845 --> 00:29:59.062
We haven't seen him in years.

207
00:30:01.700 --> 00:30:03.900
Forgive me asking.

208
00:30:03.969 --> 00:30:05.836
but how could such
a man just disappear?

209
00:30:13.528 --> 00:30:16.680
Go and eat and drink after
your long journey. Thorhall.

210
00:30:19.118 --> 00:30:20.817
We are grateful for your visit.

211
00:30:33.699 --> 00:30:36.399
I have to tell the
boys. Where are they?

212
00:30:36.468 --> 00:30:38.869
They went up to
the cabin to hunt.

213
00:31:47.839 --> 00:31:49.338
Ivar. Wake up.

214
00:31:51.944 --> 00:31:53.476
Bjorn is here.

215
00:32:09.544 --> 00:32:11.504
You think our father never knew?

216
00:32:11.746 --> 00:32:12.912
It's possible.

217
00:32:15.301 --> 00:32:18.781
In those early days. it wasn't
easy to navigate the sea.

218
00:32:18.854 --> 00:32:20.303
He knew.

219
00:32:20.372 --> 00:32:21.737
He had to.

220
00:32:21.807 --> 00:32:23.734
If he did. he should
have told the people.

221
00:32:23.758 --> 00:32:25.659
Everyone lost relatives.

222
00:32:25.727 --> 00:32:28.461
Fathers and uncles.
sons and daughters.

223
00:32:28.530 --> 00:32:29.874
They would have
demanded revenge.

224
00:32:29.898 --> 00:32:32.999
That is why he didn't tell them.

225
00:32:33.068 --> 00:32:34.988
What do you mean?
It was a waste of time.

226
00:32:36.021 --> 00:32:37.604
They were dead!

227
00:32:37.672 --> 00:32:40.273
Ragnar wanted to sail to Paris.

228
00:32:40.341 --> 00:32:41.841
He wanted to be famous.

229
00:32:41.910 --> 00:32:44.094
Isn't that more important?

230
00:32:45.547 --> 00:32:46.547
Hmm?

231
00:32:48.884 --> 00:32:49.983
You could say that?

232
00:32:50.652 --> 00:32:52.336
I can say that.

233
00:32:52.404 --> 00:32:53.470
What does that mean?

234
00:32:53.538 --> 00:32:54.778
Here's what it means.

235
00:32:55.407 --> 00:32:57.074
at least to me.

236
00:32:57.142 --> 00:32:59.076
Our father abandoned us.

237
00:32:59.144 --> 00:33:01.323
We were just
kids and he ran off.

238
00:33:01.347 --> 00:33:04.464
Only the gods
know if he's still alive.

239
00:33:04.549 --> 00:33:08.784
And now we hear he kept
this big secret from everyone.

240
00:33:09.872 --> 00:33:12.739
That he was not
truthful or honest.

241
00:33:12.808 --> 00:33:15.124
This makes me feel sick.

242
00:33:15.193 --> 00:33:18.740
How could our father not tell
the people what had happened?

243
00:33:18.764 --> 00:33:21.097
Maybe if he'd told them.
they would have killed him.

244
00:33:25.637 --> 00:33:28.038
If it's true...

245
00:33:28.106 --> 00:33:30.818
If it's true that our father lied to
his people. and abandoned them.

246
00:33:30.842 --> 00:33:33.025
then I hope he never comes back.

247
00:33:33.095 --> 00:33:34.711
He betrayed our name.

248
00:33:35.563 --> 00:33:36.713
If he ever came back.

249
00:33:38.316 --> 00:33:39.316
I would kill him.

250
00:33:40.819 --> 00:33:42.419
Me too.

251
00:33:42.488 --> 00:33:44.254
Screw you!

252
00:33:44.322 --> 00:33:46.082
All of you.

253
00:33:47.426 --> 00:33:49.559
He never did anything wrong.

254
00:33:50.662 --> 00:33:52.012
He is our father.

255
00:33:54.065 --> 00:33:55.682
And that is the end of it.

256
00:33:57.385 --> 00:34:01.138
You all sound like a
bunch of Christians.

257
00:34:03.191 --> 00:34:05.358
I love our father
as much as you do.

258
00:34:05.427 --> 00:34:07.077
Who said I loved him. Ubbe?

259
00:34:08.147 --> 00:34:09.746
I said I admired him.

260
00:34:10.749 --> 00:34:12.131
He's Viking.

261
00:34:13.802 --> 00:34:15.434
And you are soft.

262
00:34:16.021 --> 00:34:17.971
I am not soft!

263
00:34:18.040 --> 00:34:20.790
None of us is soft.

264
00:34:20.859 --> 00:34:23.292
But we want to understand
what our father did.

265
00:34:23.361 --> 00:34:25.428
and what he was.

266
00:34:25.496 --> 00:34:28.064
As his son. his fame
does not interest me.

267
00:34:29.551 --> 00:34:32.101
What he used his power for.
now that would interest me.

268
00:34:35.757 --> 00:34:39.236
By now. my brothers. there
will be a lot of anger in Kattegat.

269
00:34:39.260 --> 00:34:41.961
Now they know the truth.

270
00:34:42.030 --> 00:34:44.513
Our father betrayed a
whole generation of people.

271
00:34:44.582 --> 00:34:45.965
So if he ever came back...

272
00:34:46.034 --> 00:34:47.834
I don't think he is ever
going to come back.

273
00:34:50.322 --> 00:34:53.539
I think what happened
in Paris finally broke him.

274
00:34:55.843 --> 00:34:58.744
You can all say whatever
you want. but he was a human.

275
00:35:00.415 --> 00:35:02.282
People started to
talk as if he was a god.

276
00:35:02.350 --> 00:35:04.968
He was not a god. he was a man!

277
00:35:05.036 --> 00:35:07.086
A man with many
dreams and many failings.

278
00:35:09.524 --> 00:35:13.092
I've learned that in the
years since he went away.

279
00:35:13.161 --> 00:35:15.261
If I was him. I
wouldn't come back.

280
00:35:21.302 --> 00:35:22.936
Despite all his failings.

281
00:35:24.372 --> 00:35:26.489
he's still the greatest
man in the world to me.

282
00:36:09.183 --> 00:36:11.150
Did you know
Ragnar lied to us all?

283
00:36:13.421 --> 00:36:16.222
The settlement in Wessex was
destroyed as soon as we left.

284
00:36:23.164 --> 00:36:24.363
I know.

285
00:36:26.367 --> 00:36:28.112
A farmer who
escaped the slaughter

286
00:36:28.136 --> 00:36:30.903
told your father and I
what had happened.

287
00:36:30.973 --> 00:36:33.622
And Ragnar killed him so
no one else would find out.

288
00:36:36.744 --> 00:36:39.178
You're a good
friend to my father.

289
00:36:41.966 --> 00:36:43.083
Hello. Bjorn.

290
00:36:43.935 --> 00:36:45.084
Helga.

291
00:36:49.040 --> 00:36:51.321
I was just coming to see how
the boats were progressing.

292
00:36:53.077 --> 00:36:54.977
What do you say. Helga?

293
00:36:56.147 --> 00:36:57.830
What shall we tell him?

294
00:36:57.899 --> 00:37:00.149
We think that it won't be
long until you have boats

295
00:37:00.219 --> 00:37:02.869
ready and able to take you
to the Mediterranean Sea!

296
00:37:04.356 --> 00:37:05.955
If it exists.

297
00:37:06.024 --> 00:37:07.674
Of course it exists.

298
00:37:07.742 --> 00:37:09.341
It's just a map. Bjorn.

299
00:37:09.410 --> 00:37:12.278
Marks on a paper. A
child could have drawn it.

300
00:37:12.346 --> 00:37:13.513
How can we know it's real?

301
00:37:16.567 --> 00:37:18.251
I learned from my father.

302
00:37:20.421 --> 00:37:22.755
The only way to tell
if something is real...

303
00:37:27.696 --> 00:37:28.962
is to sail there.

304
00:37:34.535 --> 00:37:36.169
I hope you come with me. Floki.

305
00:37:37.472 --> 00:37:39.406
Are you joking?

306
00:37:39.474 --> 00:37:41.674
The lure of an imaginary land.

307
00:37:41.743 --> 00:37:43.460
Traveling somewhere
that doesn't exist.

308
00:37:45.646 --> 00:37:48.014
Of course I'm coming.

309
00:37:53.304 --> 00:37:55.349
And I hope you come too. Helga.

310
00:37:55.373 --> 00:37:59.475
Well. if Floki is mad enough
to go. then I guess I will follow.

311
00:40:34.265 --> 00:40:37.349
Let us pass. Move.

312
00:40:57.839 --> 00:40:58.855
Hello. Ivar.

313
00:41:02.026 --> 00:41:04.377
There's no mistaking you.

314
00:41:07.381 --> 00:41:10.967
It appears my return
is not welcome.

315
00:41:13.004 --> 00:41:16.524
You've obviously all made
your mind up about me.

316
00:41:19.310 --> 00:41:20.777
I cannot blame you for that.

317
00:41:24.282 --> 00:41:25.314
So.

318
00:41:26.685 --> 00:41:28.051
Well. boys.

319
00:41:29.387 --> 00:41:31.520
who is going to do it. then?

320
00:41:35.727 --> 00:41:36.809
Who's going to kill me?

321
00:41:41.099 --> 00:41:42.482
Well. I don't mind.

322
00:41:44.486 --> 00:41:45.785
Go ahead.

323
00:41:46.988 --> 00:41:48.354
Please.

324
00:41:51.042 --> 00:41:53.393
What about you. Hvitserk?

325
00:41:53.461 --> 00:41:55.428
You think you're a man now? Huh?

326
00:41:57.899 --> 00:41:59.165
I dare you.

327
00:42:02.070 --> 00:42:03.669
Put me out of my misery.

328
00:42:05.156 --> 00:42:06.156
Do it.

329
00:42:06.691 --> 00:42:08.157
Do it.

330
00:42:08.226 --> 00:42:09.559
Do it. do it. Do it!

331
00:42:11.462 --> 00:42:13.212
Look at these people!

332
00:42:14.548 --> 00:42:16.232
They no longer support me!

333
00:42:17.018 --> 00:42:18.018
Look!

334
00:42:20.322 --> 00:42:21.322
Why would they?

335
00:42:23.958 --> 00:42:26.392
I am your leader.
and I just left!

336
00:42:28.530 --> 00:42:31.197
What kind of leader
does that. huh?

337
00:42:31.265 --> 00:42:34.567
What kind of king
abandons his people?

338
00:42:44.712 --> 00:42:47.814
What kind of father
abandons his sons?

339
00:43:05.733 --> 00:43:07.466
So. who wants to be king?

340
00:43:13.842 --> 00:43:15.992
You know how this works!

341
00:43:17.162 --> 00:43:18.627
If you want to be king.

342
00:43:19.964 --> 00:43:21.297
you must kill me.

343
00:43:23.802 --> 00:43:24.802
Take it.

344
00:43:27.705 --> 00:43:28.721
No?

345
00:43:30.041 --> 00:43:31.940
You? No? What about you?

346
00:43:32.009 --> 00:43:33.259
No? No?

347
00:43:33.327 --> 00:43:34.359
Anyone?

348
00:43:36.130 --> 00:43:38.564
Who wants to be king?

348
00:43:39.305 --> 00:44:39.403
